title: About Me
text:
My current goals are to obtain my PhD in Microbiology with a primary focus on wildlife conservation, ecology, and disease. My primary focuses are on genetic disease, impacts on the normal microbiome, and emerging diseases within various wildlife species.



Undergraduate I received my B.A. from Carroll College Helena MT in 2022. I double majored in Biochemistry and Molecular Biology (BMB) as well as Biology.
Graduate I am currently a Microbiology PhD Graduate Student at the University of New Hampshire. I am within the College of Life Sciences (COLSA) and Agricultre and the department of Molecular, Cellular, and Biomedical Sciences (MCBS)
